@smorel394
Do you prefer `(i : )  M i` or ` i, M i`? We should use the same notation everywhere at least within this PR, I think.
I use the first out of habit, but I don't have a strong preference, so feel free to change it.
Why use an arbitrary set `s` rather than `` in `contDiffOn`?
In fact think that `ContinuousMultilinearMap.contDiffOn` can just be deleted, as you can easily get it by applying `ContDiff.contDiffOn` to `ContinuousMultilinearMap.contDiff`.
Everything above this can be moved to CPolynomial.lean but that's probably pointless, as that file is already longer.

When I was preparing my own PR about this, I had actually created a new file `Multilinear.lean` in `Mathlib.Analysis.Analytic`. But again, I don't have strong opinions about where to put this stuff, and I think you have way more mathlib experience than me.
